.TH "pci_find_ht_capability" 9 "pci_find_ht_capability" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_find_ht_capability \- query a device's HyperTransport capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" pci_find_ht_capability
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "int ht_cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device to query
.IP "ht_cap" 12
HyperTransport capability code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Tell if a device supports a given HyperTransport capability.
Returns an address within the device's PCI configuration space
or 0 in case the device does not support the request capability.
The address points to the PCI capability, of type PCI_CAP_ID_HT,
which has a HyperTransport capability matching \fIht_cap\fP.
